            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "After the war, many women who had entered the workforce returned to the home, where the role of wife and mother remained the ideal for women in the 1950s. Trends toward getting married earlier and having larger families reinforced the pattern of women devoting their efforts to housework and child raising rather than acquiring professional skills and pursuing careers outside the home."
